3.17:
Then to Adam He said, “Because you have listened to the voice of your wife, and have eaten from the tree about which I commanded you, saying, ‘You shall not eat from it’;
Cursed is the ground because of you;
With hard labor you shall eat from it
All the days of your life.

9.27:
May God enlarge Japheth,
And may he live in the tents of Shem;
And may Canaan be his servant.”

12.2:
And I will make you into a great nation,
And I will bless you,
And make your name great;
And you shall be a blessing;

14.19:
And he blessed him and said,
“Blessed be Abram of God Most High,
Possessor of heaven and earth;

16.12:
But he will be a wild donkey of a man;
His hand will be against everyone,
And everyone’s hand will be against him;
And he will live in defiance of all his brothers.”

17.1:
Now when Abram was ninety-nine years old, the Lord appeared to Abram and said to him,
“I am God Almighty;
Walk before Me, and be blameless.

17.5:
No longer shall you be named Abram,
But your name shall be Abraham;
For I have made you the father of a multitude of nations.

25.23:
And the Lord said to her,
“Two nations are in your womb;
And two peoples will be separated from your body;
And one people will be stronger than the other;
And the older will serve the younger.”

27.27:
So he came close and kissed him; and when he smelled the smell of his garments, he blessed him and said,
“See, the smell of my son
Is like the smell of a field which the Lord has blessed;

27.28:
Now may God give you of the dew of heaven,
And of the fatness of the earth,
And an abundance of grain and new wine;

35.11:
God also said to him,
“I am God Almighty;
Be fruitful and multiply;
A nation and a multitude of nations shall come from you,
And kings shall come from you.

48.16:
The angel who has redeemed me from all evil,
Bless the boys;
And may my name live on in them,
And the names of my fathers Abraham and Isaac;
And may they grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.”

49.4:
Uncontrollable as water, you shall not have preeminence,
Because you went up to your father’s bed;
Then you defiled it—he went up to my couch.

49.6:
May my soul not enter into their council;
May my glory not be united with their assembly;
For in their anger they killed men,
And in their self-will they lamed oxen.

49.8:
“As for you, Judah, your brothers shall praise you;
Your hand shall be on the neck of your enemies;
Your father’s sons shall bow down to you.

49.13:
“Zebulun will reside at the seashore;
And he shall be a harbor for ships,
And his flank shall be toward Sidon.

49.22:
“Joseph is a fruitful branch,
A fruitful branch by a spring;
Its branches hang over a wall.

49.27:
“Benjamin is a ravenous wolf;
In the morning he devours the prey,
And in the evening he divides the spoils.”
